abstract: Coronavirus, Harvey Weinstein verdict, Kanye West: Here’s what you need to know.

abstract: The Trump administration rolled out a new immigration policy on Monday that bars people deemed likely to require government benefits such as housing and food assistance from obtaining permanent residency in the United States.
snippet: The Trump administration rolled out a new immigration policy on Monday that bars people deemed likely to require government benefits such as housing and food assistance from obtaining permanent residency in the United States.
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — The Trump administration rolled out a new immigration policy on Monday that bars people deemed likely to require government benefits such as housing and food assistance from obtaining permanent residency in the United States.
headline_main: New U.S. Rule Targeting Poor Immigrants Sows Fear, Confusion, Advocates Say
headline_print_headline: New U.S. Rule Targeting Poor Immigrants Sows Fear, Confusion, Advocates Say

abstract: As concerns over the spreading coronavirus outbreak hammered U.S. stocks, one corner of the market was confronted with another potentially game-changing prospect: a Bernie Sanders nomination.

abstract: Central bankers and administration officials alike are unsure how the virus will affect American economic growth.
snippet: Central bankers and administration officials alike are unsure how the virus will affect American economic growth.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — As an uptick in the number of coronavirus infections outside China sent markets swooning on Monday, attention quickly turned to how the Federal Reserve and the United States government would assess — and even address — the economic fallout.

abstract: The U.N. Security Council on Monday reiterated its support for a two-state solution to the Israeli-Palestinian conflict, in its first statement following the unveiling of the U.S. plan for resolving the decades-old struggle three weeks ago.
snippet: The U.N. Security Council on Monday reiterated its support for a two-state solution to the Israeli-Palestinian conflict, in its first statement following the unveiling of the U.S. plan for resolving the decades-old struggle three weeks ago.
lead_paragraph: UNITED NATIONS — The U.N. Security Council on Monday reiterated its support for a two-state solution to the Israeli-Palestinian conflict, in its first statement following the unveiling of the U.S. plan for resolving the decades-old struggle three weeks ago.
headline_main: UN Reiterates Support for 2-State Israel-Palestine Solution
headline_print_headline: UN Reiterates Support for 2-State Israel-Palestine Solution

abstract: U.S. President Donald Trump has decided to step up a sanctions campaign on Venezuela's oil sector and will be more aggressive in punishing people and companies that violate it, the top U.S. envoy to the Latin American country said on Monday.
snippet: U.S. President Donald Trump has decided to step up a sanctions campaign on Venezuela's oil sector and will be more aggressive in punishing people and companies that violate it, the top U.S. envoy to the Latin American country said on Monday.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — U.S. President Donald Trump has decided to step up a sanctions campaign on Venezuela's oil sector and will be more aggressive in punishing people and companies that violate it, the top U.S. envoy to the Latin American country said on Monday.
headline_main: Trump Administration to Step Up Pressure Campaign on Venezuelan Oil - US Envoy
headline_print_headline: Trump Administration to Step Up Pressure Campaign on Venezuelan Oil - US Envoy

abstract: A sharply divided federal appeals court on Monday said the Trump administration may enforce a rule labeled by critics as a "gag rule" that could deprive abortion providers of federal funding for family planning.
snippet: A sharply divided federal appeals court on Monday said the Trump administration may enforce a rule labeled by critics as a "gag rule" that could deprive abortion providers of federal funding for family planning.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - A sharply divided federal appeals court on Monday said the Trump administration may enforce a rule labeled by critics as a "gag rule" that could deprive abortion providers of federal funding for family planning.
headline_main: Trump 'Gag Rule' on Abortion Referral Can Be Enforced, U.S. Appeals Court Rules
headline_print_headline: Trump 'Gag Rule' on Abortion Referral Can Be Enforced, U.S. Appeals Court Rules

abstract: Democratic presidential hopeful Michael Bloomberg on Monday clashed with front-runner Bernie Sanders over vandalism at Bloomberg's Chicago office and their gun control stances, while centrist rival Pete Buttigieg was heckled at a labor march.
snippet: Democratic presidential hopeful Michael Bloomberg on Monday clashed with front-runner Bernie Sanders over vandalism at Bloomberg's Chicago office and their gun control stances, while centrist rival Pete Buttigieg was heckled at a labor march.
lead_paragraph: CHARLESTON, S.C. — Democratic presidential hopeful Michael Bloomberg on Monday clashed with front-runner Bernie Sanders over vandalism at Bloomberg's Chicago office and their gun control stances, while centrist rival Pete Buttigieg was heckled at a labor march.
headline_main: On the Trail: Buttigieg Heckled, Bloomberg and Sanders Tussle on Vandalism, Guns
headline_print_headline: On the Trail: Buttigieg Heckled, Bloomberg and Sanders Tussle on Vandalism, Guns

abstract: Bernie Sanders told “60 Minutes” that it would be “unfair” to say “everything is bad” about Cuba’s Communist revolution.
snippet: Bernie Sanders told “60 Minutes” that it would be “unfair” to say “everything is bad” about Cuba’s Communist revolution.
lead_paragraph: MIAMI — Comments from Senator Bernie Sanders praising aspects of the Communist Cuban revolution drew a forceful rebuke on Monday from Cuban-Americans, Florida Democrats and several of Mr. Sanders’s opponents, who cast him as too extreme in his views to represent the party as its presidential nominee.
